history.content:
Hello everyone!

Are you still looking for one or two units to fill out your semester? Interested in helping out students during lab? Look no further! The 61C staff is currently looking for interested and qualified individuals for academic intern (formerly lab assistant) positions. If you liked CS61C and want to spread the love, this is your chance to give back to the class (and potentially gain the experience to be a TA in the future)!

 

Benefits include

  • Getting one or two units of P/NP credit
  • Receiving mentorship from course staff at weekly family meetings!
  • Great opportunity to solidify your understanding of course material

 

If this perks your interest, please apply through this google form link here no later than Wednesday, January 30th at 11:59PM PST. Decisions will be sent out within the next two days!
history.subject: CS61C Academic Intern Application
